      • isScheduledSendAfterDay

        public static boolean isScheduledSendAfterDay(java.util.Date scheduledSend,
                                              java.util.Date dueDate)
        This method was introduced to provide a consistant interface for determining if a check has been sent already. In particular, CheckImpl and TransactionBasedFinancialsCalculator had been using different date comparisons in determining if a check had already been sent by a date
        Parameters:
        scheduledSend - the date the check is scheduled to be sent
        dueDate - the date for comparison.
        Returns:
        boolean Returns true if the day the check is to be sent is after the given due date
